

ctsockets
=========

CTSockets is part of the Terca C++ libraries.
Terca C++ sockets provide a very basic TCP server and client.
It uses a variety of defaults in order to simplify usage.
It is not designed to be multithreaded as this time.

Installing
==========

This library uses a standard makefile.
Note that if you are not on a GNU/Linux system, you will
probably need to change the install directories. You may
also need to change compilers. The default is set to gcc.
To build and install use:

make
sudo make install

Dependancies
============

Terca C++ Sockets uses GnuTLS to provide AES.
GnuTLS is licensed under LGPLv2.1+ and copyrighted by Free Software Foundation, Inc.
Please see http://www.gnutls.org/ for more information

